info.title: OData Service for namespace microsoft.graph
info.description: This OData service is located at https://graph.microsoft.com/v1.0

/chats.description: Provides operations to manage the collection of chat entities.

get.description: Retrieve the list of chats that the user is part of. This method supports federation. When a user ID is provided, the calling application must belong to the same tenant that the user belongs to.

/chats/{chat-id}/members.description: Provides operations to manage the members property of the microsoft.graph.chat entity.

get.description: Retrieve a conversationMember from a chat or channel.

post.description: Add a conversationMember to a chat.

/chats/{chat-id}/members/{conversationMe.description: Provides operations to manage the members property of the microsoft.graph.chat entity.

get.description: Retrieve a conversationMember from a chat or channel.

patch.summary: Update the navigation property members in chats

delete.description: Remove a conversationMember from a chat.

/chats/{chat-id}/messages.description: Provides operations to manage the messages property of the microsoft.graph.chat entity.

get.description: Retrieve the list of messages in a chat. This method supports federation. To list chat messages in application context, the request must be made from the tenant that the channel owner belongs to (represented by the **tenantId** property on the channel).

post.summary: Send chatMessage in a channel or a chat
post.description: Send a new chatMessage in the specified channel or a chat.

/chats/{chat-id}/messages/{chatMessage-i.description: Provides operations to manage the messages property of the microsoft.graph.chat entity.

get.summary: Get chatMessage in a channel or chat
get.description: Retrieve a single message or a message reply in a channel or a chat.

patch.summary: Update the navigation property messages in chats

delete.summary: Delete navigation property messages for chats

/me/joinedTeams.description: Provides operations to manage the joinedTeams property of the microsoft.graph.user entity.

get.description: Get the teams in Microsoft Teams that the user is a direct member of.

/teams.description: Provides operations to manage the collection of team entities.

/teams/{team-id}.description: Provides operations to manage the collection of team entities.

get.summary: Get entity from teams by key

patch.description: Update the properties of the specified team.

/teams/{team-id}/allChannels.description: Provides operations to manage the allChannels property of the microsoft.graph.team entity.

get.description: Get the list of channels either in this team or shared with this team (incoming channels).

/teams/{team-id}/allChannels/{channel-id.description: Provides operations to manage the allChannels property of the microsoft.graph.team entity.

get.description: List of channels either hosted in or shared with the team (incoming channels).

/teams/{team-id}/channels.description: Provides operations to manage the channels property of the microsoft.graph.team entity.

get.description: Retrieve the list of channels in this team.

post.description: Create a new channel in a team, as specified in the request body.  When you create a channel, the maximum length of the channel's `displayName` is 50 characters. This is the name that appears to the user in Microsoft Teams. If you're creating a private channel, you can add a maximum of 200 members.

/teams/{team-id}/channels/{channel-id}.description: Provides operations to manage the channels property of the microsoft.graph.team entity.

get.description: Retrieve the properties and relationships of a channel. This method supports federation. Only a user who is a member of the shared channel can retrieve channel information.

/teams/{team-id}/channels/{channel-id}/m.description: Provides operations to manage the members property of the microsoft.graph.channel entity.

get.description: Retrieve a list of conversationMembers from a channel. This method supports federation. Only a user who is a member of the shared channel can retrieve the channel member list.

post.description: Add a conversationMember to a channel.

/teams/{team-id}/channels/{channel-id}/m.description: Provides operations to manage the members property of the microsoft.graph.channel entity.

get.description: Get a conversationMember from a channel.

patch.description: Update the role of a conversationMember in a team or channel.

delete.description: Delete a conversationMember from a channel. This operation is allowed only for channels with a **membershipType** value of `private` or `shared`.

/teams/{team-id}/channels/{channel-id}/m.description: Provides operations to manage the messages property of the microsoft.graph.channel entity.

get.description: Retrieve the list of messages (without the replies) in a channel of a team.  To get the replies for a message, call the list message replies or the get message reply API.  This method supports federation. To list channel messages in application context, the request must be made from the tenant that the channel owner belongs to (represented by the **tenantId** property on the channel).

post.summary: Send chatMessage in a channel or a chat
post.description: Send a new chatMessage in the specified channel or a chat.

/teams/{team-id}/channels/{channel-id}/m.description: Provides operations to manage the messages property of the microsoft.graph.channel entity.

get.summary: Get chatMessage in a channel or chat
get.description: Retrieve a single message or a message reply in a channel or a chat.

delete.summary: Delete navigation property messages for teams

id.description: The unique idenfier for an entity. Read-only.

createdDateTime.description: Date and time at which the chat was created. Read-only.

lastUpdatedDateTime.description: Date and time at which the chat was renamed or list of members were last changed. Read-only.

onlineMeetingInfo.description: Represents details about an online meeting. If the chat isn't associated with an online meeting, the property is empty. Read-only.

tenantId.description: The identifier of the tenant in which the chat was created. Read-only.

topic.description: (Optional) Subject or topic for the chat. Only available for group chats.

viewpoint.description: Represents caller-specific information about the chat, such as last message read date and time. This property is populated only when the request is made in a delegated context.

webUrl.description: The URL for the chat in Microsoft Teams. The URL should be treated as an opaque blob, and not parsed. Read-only.

installedApps.description: A collection of all the apps in the chat. Nullable.

lastMessagePreview.description: Preview of the last message sent in the chat. Null if no messages have been sent in the chat. Currently, only the list chats operation supports this property.

members.description: A collection of all the members in the chat. Nullable.

messages.description: A collection of all the messages in the chat. Nullable.

pinnedMessages.description: A collection of all the pinned messages in the chat. Nullable.

tabs.description: A collection of all the tabs in the chat. Nullable.

classification.description: An optional label. Typically describes the data or business sensitivity of the team. Must match one of a pre-configured set in the tenant's directory.

createdDateTime.description: Timestamp at which the team was created.

description.description: An optional description for the team. Maximum length: 1024 characters.

funSettings.description: Settings to configure use of Giphy, memes, and stickers in the team.

guestSettings.description: Settings to configure whether guests can create, update, or delete channels in the team.

internalId.description: A unique ID for the team that has been used in a few places such as the audit log/Office 365 Management Activity API.

isArchived.description: Whether this team is in read-only mode.

memberSettings.description: Settings to configure whether members can perform certain actions, for example, create channels and add bots, in the team.

messagingSettings.description: Settings to configure messaging and mentions in the team.

specialization.description: Optional. Indicates whether the team is intended for a particular use case.  Each team specialization has access to unique behaviors and experiences targeted to its use case.

summary.description: Contains summary information about the team, including number of owners, members, and guests.

tenantId.description: The ID of the Azure Active Directory tenant.

visibility.description: The visibility of the group and team. Defaults to Public.

webUrl.description: A hyperlink that will go to the team in the Microsoft Teams client. This is the URL that you get when you right-click a team in the Microsoft Teams client and select Get link to team. This URL should be treated as an opaque blob, and not parsed.

allChannels.description: List of channels either hosted in or shared with the team (incoming channels).

channels.description: The collection of channels and messages associated with the team.

incomingChannels.description: List of channels shared with the team.

installedApps.description: The apps installed in this team.

members.description: Members and owners of the team.

operations.description: The async operations that ran or are running on this team.

photo.description: The profile photo for the team.

primaryChannel.description: The general channel for the team.

tags.description: The tags associated with the team.

template.description: The template this team was created from. See available templates.

schedule.description: The schedule of shifts for this team.

createdDateTime.description: Read only. Timestamp at which the channel was created.

description.description: Optional textual description for the channel.

displayName.description: Channel name as it will appear to the user in Microsoft Teams. The maximum length is 50 characters.

email.description: The email address for sending messages to the channel. Read-only.

isFavoriteByDefault.description: Indicates whether the channel should automatically be marked 'favorite' for all members of the team. Can only be set programmatically with Create team. Default: false.

membershipType.description: The type of the channel. Can be set during creation and can't be changed. The possible values are: standard, private, unknownFutureValue, shared. The default value is standard. Note that you must use the Prefer: include-unknown-enum-members request header to get the following value in this evolvable enum: shared.

tenantId.description: The ID of the Azure Active Directory tenant.

webUrl.description: A hyperlink that will go to the channel in Microsoft Teams. This is the URL that you get when you right-click a channel in Microsoft Teams and select Get link to channel. This URL should be treated as an opaque blob, and not parsed. Read-only.

filesFolder.description: Metadata for the location where the channel's files are stored.

members.description: A collection of membership records associated with the channel.

messages.description: A collection of all the messages in the channel. A navigation property. Nullable.

sharedWithTeams.description: A collection of teams with which a channel is shared.

tabs.description: A collection of all the tabs in the channel. A navigation property.

teamsAppDefinition.description: The details of this version of the app.

displayName.description: The display name of the user.

roles.description: The roles for that user. This property only contains additional qualifiers when relevant - for example, if the member has owner privileges, the roles property contains owner as one of the values. Similarly, if the member is a guest, the roles property contains guest as one of the values. A basic member should not have any values specified in the roles property.

visibleHistoryStartDateTime.description: The timestamp denoting how far back a conversation's history is shared with the conversation member. This property is settable only for members of a chat.

attemptsCount.description: Number of times the operation was attempted before being marked successful or failed.

createdDateTime.description: Time when the operation was created.

error.description: Any error that causes the async operation to fail.

lastActionDateTime.description: Time when the async operation was last updated.

targetResourceId.description: The ID of the object that's created or modified as result of this async operation, typically a team.

targetResourceLocation.description: The location of the object that's created or modified as result of this async operation. This URL should be treated as an opaque value and not parsed into its component paths.

description.description: The description of the tag as it will appear to the user in Microsoft Teams. A teamworkTag can't have more than 200 teamworkTagMembers.

displayName.description: The name of the tag as it will appear to the user in Microsoft Teams.

memberCount.description: The number of users assigned to the tag.

tagType.description: The type of the tag. Default is standard.

teamId.description: ID of the team in which the tag is defined.

tenantId.description: The ID of the Azure Active Directory tenant.

attachments.description: References to attached objects like files, tabs, meetings etc.

channelIdentity.description: If the message was sent in a channel, represents identity of the channel.

chatId.description: If the message was sent in a chat, represents the identity of the chat.

createdDateTime.description: Timestamp of when the chat message was created.

deletedDateTime.description: Read only. Timestamp at which the chat message was deleted, or null if not deleted.

etag.description: Read-only. Version number of the chat message.

eventDetail.description: Read-only. If present, represents details of an event that happened in a chat, a channel, or a team, for example, adding new members. For event messages, the messageType property will be set to systemEventMessage.

from.description: Details of the sender of the chat message. Can only be set during migration.

lastEditedDateTime.description: Read only. Timestamp when edits to the chat message were made. Triggers an 'Edited' flag in the Teams UI. If no edits are made the value is null.

lastModifiedDateTime.description: Read only. Timestamp when the chat message is created (initial setting) or modified, including when a reaction is added or removed.

locale.description: Locale of the chat message set by the client. Always set to en-us.

mentions.description: List of entities mentioned in the chat message. Supported entities are: user, bot, team, and channel.

policyViolation.description: Defines the properties of a policy violation set by a data loss prevention (DLP) application.

reactions.description: Reactions for this chat message (for example, Like).

replyToId.description: Read-only. ID of the parent chat message or root chat message of the thread. (Only applies to chat messages in channels, not chats.)

subject.description: The subject of the chat message, in plaintext.

summary.description: Summary text of the chat message that could be used for push notifications and summary views or fall back views. Only applies to channel chat messages, not chat messages in a chat.

webUrl.description: Read-only. Link to the message in Microsoft Teams.

hostedContents.description: Content in a message hosted by Microsoft Teams - for example, images or code snippets.

replies.description: Replies for a specified message. Supports $expand for channel messages.

isHostTeam.description: Indicates whether the team is the host of the channel.

allowedMembers.description: A collection of team members who have access to the shared channel.

configuration.description: Container for custom settings applied to a tab. The tab is considered configured only once this property is set.

webUrl.description: Deep link URL of the tab instance. Read only.

teamsApp.description: The application that is linked to the tab. This cannot be changed after tab creation.

message.description: Represents details about the chat message that is pinned.

contentBytes.description: Write only. Bytes for the hosted content (such as images).

contentType.description: Write only. Content type. sicj as image/png, image/jpg.

tenantId.description: The ID of the tenant that the tag member is a part of.

userId.description: The user ID of the member.

contentType.description: The type of the content. Possible values are text and html.

request-id.description: Request Id as tracked internally by the service

client-request-id.description: Client request Id as sent by the client application.

BaseCollectionPaginationCountResponse.title: Base collection pagination and count responses

top.name: $top
top.description: Show only the first n items
